    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@he852100, _implicit_ formatting _never_ automatically line-wraps _values_ (only _column headers_), only piping to `Format-Table -Wrap` does.\r\n\r\nThere is a small bug in the formatter, however: with only _one_ character to show, it should show the ellipsis (`â€¦`), not the first character of the value:\r\n\r\n```powershell\r\nPS> [pscustomobject] @{  ('a' *([console]::WindowWidth - 3)) = 'abc'; 'b' = 'def' }\r\naaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa b\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------- -\r\nabc                                                                           d\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat is, instead of `d` you should see `â€¦` in the above output.\r\n",
